09/07/2003
OTTAWA, Canada -- Prime Minister Jean Chretien will meet his Romanian counterpart, Adrian Nastase, on the sidelines of an international conference in London later this week to discuss the possible sale of two more nuclear reactors. An international consortium led by Atomic Energy Canada has already built two Candu reactors in Romania, at a cost of $700m each. Bucharest has approached Canada for help in the continuation of its nuclear energy programme. (AFP - 08/07/03)
